org.orgName: United States District Court For The Western District of Washington Northern Division

div1.p: Wherefore complainant prays that a writ of Habeas Corpus issue herein directed in said defendant David Marsh command ring him forth with to bring and have complainant before his honor the said S.C. Wingard Judge of said Court as aforesaid at his chambers in Colfax in said Judicial District that the cause of his said restraint may be inquired into and that he may be dealt with according to law
L.D. Woeford Attorney for the Complainant
Territory of Washington County of Whitman}ss
Dan Sullivan being duly sworn says the above named complainant that I have heard read the foregoing complaint read and know the content thereof and the same is true as I verily believe
Subscribed and sworn to before me this 13th day of June A.D. 1881 A. Reeves Hynes Clerk Dist. Court
